<p>to the 3rd Batt. band which <strike>was play</strike> practised "The Arcadians" &amp; "Cavalierio" by the side of the road which runs between cliff &amp; marsh to Moscourt.</p>
<p>[Note in margin]  Chippily</p>
<p>The landscape there is a trifle more inspiring than ours here. The white cliffs under which the chaps were camped in dug outs, &amp; the green rushy marsh with plenty of fairly healthy looking trees combined to vary my outlook &amp; made me feel more confident &amp; less bored. Even there, however, I discovered a horses hoof &amp; broken limber wheel hidden in the grass. It reminded me of XXX</p>
<p>"Such things you know must always be<br/>After a famous victory."</p>
